PRETORIA – The price of all grades of petrol will increase by 67c/l with effect from midnight on the fifth of September, the energy department said on Sunday. The price of diesel, both 0.05% sulphur and 0.005% sulphur, would increase by 44.00c/l, the department said in a statement. READ:  AA anticipates another petrol price hike The wholesale price of illuminating paraffin would increase by 49c/l, and the single maximum national retail price (SMNRP) by 65c/l. The maximum LPGas retail price would increase by 86c/kg. The department said the main reasons for the fuel price adjustments were that the rand depreciated, on average, against the US dollar during the period under review, and that the international prices of petroleum products increased on average during the same time. African News Agency